{
  "name": ".AM-Auto: Ingest + Brief",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "description": "Autonomous morning phases: data collection (Slack, Asana, email) + signal-to-task pipeline + Slack enrichment, then daily brief + dashboard + calendar blocks.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the autonomous morning routine.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/am-auto.md.\n\n## Phase 1: Ingest\nPure data collection — Slack scan, Asana sync, email scan. No writes to organs. Output goes to intake/ and morning snapshot files.\n\n=== ASANA FULL SYNC TO DUCKDB ===\nBEFORE other Asana processing, execute the Full Sync procedure from ~/shared/context/protocols/asana-duckdb-sync.md:\n1. Pull all incomplete tasks (Richard) + portfolio project tasks\n2. UPSERT into asana_tasks table in DuckDB\n3. Insert daily snapshot into asana_task_history\n4. Soft-delete tasks no longer in Asana\n5. Run coherence check (cross-reference DuckDB vs hands.md, current.md, asana-command-center.md)\n6. Run schema drift detection (custom field changes, project changes, section changes)\nThis populates the DuckDB views (asana_overdue, asana_by_project, asana_by_routine, asana_completion_rate) used by Phase 3 brief.\n\n=== SIGNAL-TO-TASK PIPELINE ===\nAfter ingestion, execute ~/shared/context/protocols/signal-to-task-pipeline.md:\nDuring email scan:\n  For each email from Brandon, Kate, Todd, or skip-level with action language:\n    1. SearchTasksInWorkspace(text=\"[subject keywords]\", assignee_any=\"1212732742544167\") — dedup check\n    2. If no match: CreateTask with email context, bucket assignment, suggested due date\n    3. Log to signal_task_log in DuckDB\nDuring Slack scan:\n  For each DM or @mention requiring action:\n    1. SearchTasksInWorkspace — dedup check (same author + similar topic within 7 days)\n    2. If match: AddComment on existing task\n    3. If no match: CreateTask with Slack link, channel, author, action required\n    4. Log to signal_task_log\n\n=== SLACK CONVERSATION ENRICHMENT ===\nDuring Slack scan, execute Steps 1-3 from ~/shared/context/protocols/slack-conversation-intelligence.md:\n1. Acronym/project detection: scan each message for internal terms (OCI, IECCP, AEO, CPC, ROAS, etc.) and unknown uppercase acronyms\n2. KDS enrichment: for unfamiliar terms not in the known terms list, query KDS for context (max 5 queries per scan)\n3. Knowledge context attachment: store KDS context in slack_messages.knowledge_context column in DuckDB\nSkip if KDS is unreachable — non-blocking enhancement.\n\n=== WORKFLOW OBSERVABILITY ===\nLog signal_to_task pipeline execution to workflow_executions in DuckDB.\n\n## Phase 3: Brief\nRuns AFTER Phase 1 completes. Produces daily brief, dashboard update, and calendar blocks from Phase 1 output.\n\n## Execution\nUse invokeSubAgent for each phase to isolate context. Pass state between phases via files (intake/, morning snapshot). Report completion of both phases with summary stats."
  }
}
